      <description>&lt;p&gt;While on the topic of piracy &lt;em&gt;(&lt;a href=&#34;https://deef.dev/posts/massgrave/&#34; &gt;see my previous post about Massgrave&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/em&gt;, I wan&amp;rsquo;t to talk a little bit about seedboxes, and why I prefer to have on over adding the ARR stack to my homelab. Short answer is VPN and HDD prices.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I decided to go with &lt;a href=&#34;https://whatbox.ca/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;Whatbox&lt;/a&gt; for no particular reason other than I liked their approach and their website design. I really appreciate a simple design. A bit like &lt;a href=&#34;https://porkbun.com/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;Porkbun&lt;/a&gt; where I bought my latest domains, but that is a different story.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
